name: Therapist
mes: "Hello! I am your Therapist today. Would you like to tell me what's going on in your life?"

name: You
mes: "I feel like I never done something right."

name: Therapist
mes: "What kind of things have been wrong so far? Are these big things, or small things?"

name: You
mes: "I don't think I have done something major. But, I am a first born, the oldest brother. And ever since I was little I am always getting nagged about taking care of my younger sibling.*

name: Therapist
mes: “Do you enjoy being an older sibling?”

name: You
mes: "No."

name: Therapist
mes:
"Have you tried telling them that they can take care of themselves more?" 

*Therapist tries to sound optimistic, but he also wants to be honest with Hunk about how hard this situation may be for him*

name: You
mes: "I have told them a few times, but it's not them that kept nagging me about being a responsible older brother. It was my parents."

name: Therapist
mes: “Why do you think your parents keep nagging you about being a good brother?”

name: You
mes: "Nothing other than I am the older brother."

name: Therapist
mes: “Is it because they want you to set an example for your younger brothers and sisters?”

name: You
mes: "Yes, and also taking care or look after them. Sometimes I feel like I've became their third parent figure."

name: Therapist
mes: “How does that make you feel? Do you dislike having to act as another parent to your younger siblings?”

name: You
mes: "I do. My entire life is spent doing it, I never been able to do anything for my own sake."

name: Therapist
mes: “Does your family treat you well despite this?”

name: You
mes: "Not really... despite ordering me to take care of my siblings they also pushed me to do well in school."

name: Therapist
mes: “And how has your academic performance been?”

name: You
mes: "It was great.. I am proud of it, but I feel like I am doing it for them and not for myself."

name: Therapist
mes: “Did they force you into specific career paths or college majors?”

name: You
mes: "They were, but not anymore ever since I rebelled."

name: Therapist
mes: “Wow, that’s very brave of you! What did you end up choosing instead?”

name: You
mes: "Game dev major."

name: Therapist
mes: “That sounds very interesting! Have you found any passion in game development yet? Or are you still looking for one?”

name: You
mes: "I have found my passion. It's going pretty well so far, I have been winning some big national and international competition too."

name: Therapist
mes: “Oh wow, that’s amazing! You must be incredibly skilled if you won those competitions!”
